for your third year working at Xuan Island.

284
00:12:55,000 --> 00:12:55,720
An amusement park?

285
00:12:56,240 --> 00:12:57,200
Mr. Ye invested it
a few years ago.

286
00:12:58,240 --> 00:12:59,440
It's reviews are great.

287
00:12:59,919 --> 00:13:00,399
I can set you up

288
00:13:00,399 --> 00:13:01,639
with the full package

289
00:13:01,679 --> 00:13:03,039
— meals, lodging, and transport.

290
00:13:05,759 --> 00:13:06,919
It's a nice place, sure.

291
00:13:07,200 --> 00:13:08,039
But I don't have time.

292
00:13:08,759 --> 00:13:10,000
Hey, I arranged it just for you,

293
00:13:10,000 --> 00:13:10,720
and you're not going?

294
00:13:11,960 --> 00:13:12,919
That's very kind of you,

295
00:13:13,279 --> 00:13:14,240
but I'm good.

296
00:13:15,919 --> 00:13:16,840
Won't you reconsider?

297
00:13:18,559 --> 00:13:20,279
Xuan Island brings in business these days.

298
00:13:20,399 --> 00:13:21,919
Qing Ye asked me to help her hand out flyers.

299
00:13:24,519 --> 00:13:25,000
Fine.

300
00:13:27,519 --> 00:13:28,120
Take this,

301
00:13:28,399 --> 00:13:29,159
you shall go with Quanya.

302
00:13:29,639 --> 00:13:30,720
I'll help you load these into the car.

303
00:13:51,519 --> 00:13:52,200
Wu.

304
00:13:53,080 --> 00:13:53,840
Where's Shu Han?

305
00:13:54,679 --> 00:13:55,799
I'm here, Auntie.

306
00:13:56,480 --> 00:13:57,480
Oh, Shu Han,

307
00:13:57,480 --> 00:13:59,000
it's good to see you came back.

308
00:13:59,320 --> 00:14:01,279
The moment you returned, my sun came out.

309
00:14:01,360 --> 00:14:02,279
The moment you returned,
my son

310
00:14:02,720 --> 00:14:03,720
finally has work to do.

311
00:14:04,960 --> 00:14:06,519
You're really a fortune cat* for our family.
[*Chinese figurine symbolizing wealth]

312
00:14:06,919 --> 00:14:07,600
A lucky cat.

313
00:14:09,320 --> 00:14:10,639
Come on, Auntie.

314
00:14:10,840 --> 00:14:12,440
Wu is actually my fortune god.

315
00:14:12,559 --> 00:14:13,960
We make money together.

316
00:14:14,000 --> 00:14:14,519
It's great.

317
00:14:14,840 --> 00:14:16,200
Exactly, exactly.

318
00:14:16,279 --> 00:14:17,600
Making money, money.

319
00:14:17,919 --> 00:14:20,440
Fortune cat and fortune god are well matched.

320
00:14:21,759 --> 00:14:22,519
In your eyes,

321
00:14:22,559 --> 00:14:23,559
Zhao Pock and Joey Wong
are a perfect match, too.

322
00:14:24,759 --> 00:14:25,639
They are well matched, yeah.

323
00:14:25,840 --> 00:14:26,600
but Zhao Pock
can't get Joey Wong.

324
00:14:27,480 --> 00:14:28,320
So what can I do?

325
00:14:29,080 --> 00:14:30,159
Look, Shuhan's back.

326
00:14:30,159 --> 00:14:31,360
Shouldn't you hurry up and

327
00:14:31,399 --> 00:14:33,159
treat her to a welcome-back dinner?

328
00:14:33,639 --> 00:14:34,159
Fine.

329
00:14:35,240 --> 00:14:36,279
Let's invite Qing Ye along too.

330
00:14:40,039 --> 00:14:41,320
Well, then it has to be my treat.

331
00:14:41,600 --> 00:14:43,159
As the host, I should welcome my cousin.

332
00:14:43,600 --> 00:14:44,159
Qing Ye,

333
00:14:44,399 --> 00:14:45,639
what kind of food are you into?

334
00:14:47,159 --> 00:14:48,279
Well, I don't really

335
00:14:48,600 --> 00:14:49,679
have an appetite, so...

336
00:14:49,720 --> 00:14:50,279
and I need to sort out the flyers.
Who caught your eye, huh?

337
00:14:52,039 --> 00:14:52,840
Be serious.

338
00:14:54,799 --> 00:14:55,440
No appetite

339
00:14:55,440 --> 00:14:56,639
exactly means you shall go out for some good.

340
00:14:57,240 --> 00:14:58,159
Exactly.

341
00:14:58,679 --> 00:14:59,320
How about this

342
00:14:59,519 --> 00:15:00,919
— we go to Granny Zhao's café

343
00:15:00,919 --> 00:15:01,600
for some dessert.

344
00:15:01,840 --> 00:15:03,000
I happen to have brought her some

345
00:15:03,000 --> 00:15:03,919
coffee beans from Hainan.

346
00:15:04,480 --> 00:15:05,000
How about it?

347
00:15:07,039 --> 00:15:07,559
Fine.

348
00:15:07,840 --> 00:15:08,919
I gotta thank my sister-in-law.

349
00:15:11,559 --> 00:15:12,320
Don't say that nonsense.

350
00:15:14,039 --> 00:15:14,799
You little brat...

351
00:15:15,720 --> 00:15:16,399
Let's go, go.

352
00:15:19,919 --> 00:15:20,360
Go.

353
00:15:24,519 --> 00:15:25,039
Ye.

354
00:15:26,919 --> 00:15:27,399
Um,

355
00:15:28,279 --> 00:15:29,559
I still have

356
00:15:29,759 --> 00:15:30,559
200 yuan.
Take it,

357
00:15:32,000 --> 00:15:33,759
and keep an eye on Wu for me in a bit.

358
00:15:34,039 --> 00:15:35,159
Don't let the girl pay.

359
00:15:37,240 --> 00:15:37,799
I get it.

360
00:15:38,720 --> 00:15:39,200
Go on.

361
00:15:45,960 --> 00:15:47,159
Ah, to be young.

362
00:15:48,480 --> 00:15:50,759
Tofu for sale!

363
00:15:51,720 --> 00:15:54,080
Freshly made tofu!

364
00:15:54,759 --> 00:15:55,639
Thank you, Granny.

365
00:15:56,000 --> 00:15:56,600
Here, let me.

366
00:15:56,720 --> 00:15:58,279
Thanks, Granny. This's for Qing Ye.

367
00:15:58,600 --> 00:16:00,200
Here, This's yours.

368
00:16:00,200 --> 00:16:00,679
Okay.

369
00:16:01,120 --> 00:16:01,799
This one's yours.

370
00:16:01,799 --> 00:16:02,919
Thank you, Granny Zhao.

371
00:16:03,360 --> 00:16:03,919
Hey, Granny.
Well, I

372
00:16:04,840 --> 00:16:06,519
brought you beans from Hainan.

373
00:16:07,360 --> 00:16:08,519
Try them later.

374
00:16:08,600 --> 00:16:09,639
If they're good,

375
00:16:09,639 --> 00:16:10,440
just let me know.
I'll bring you more next time.

376
00:16:11,960 --> 00:16:13,000
Thank you so much.

377
00:16:13,600 --> 00:16:14,679
It's all thanks to you always bringing me

378
00:16:14,679 --> 00:16:15,639
such good beans.

379
00:16:15,720 --> 00:16:16,519
It's nothing.

380
00:16:17,039 --> 00:16:19,159
These are the best coffee and

381
00:16:19,600 --> 00:16:20,320
desserts in our shop.

382
00:16:20,480 --> 00:16:22,000
Today, it's my treat!

383
00:16:22,279 --> 00:16:22,960
Hey, no way.

384
00:16:23,080 --> 00:16:24,000
It's my treat, my treat.

385
00:16:24,200 --> 00:16:24,919
Grandma Zhao,

386
00:16:25,320 --> 00:16:26,679
This looks absolutely beautiful.

387
00:16:27,159 --> 00:16:28,759
Who did you learn to make coffee from?

388
00:16:29,279 --> 00:16:30,360
I learned it from my son.

389
00:16:30,919 --> 00:16:32,480
After my son graduated from college,

390
00:16:32,759 --> 00:16:34,240
he wanted to open a café

391
00:16:34,440 --> 00:16:36,159
here in Zhazhating.

392
00:16:36,720 --> 00:16:37,679
But who around there

393
00:16:37,720 --> 00:16:39,200
even has a taste for coffee?

394
00:16:39,519 --> 00:16:40,200
They all said

395
00:16:40,360 --> 00:16:41,919
it tasted like herbal medicine.

396
00:16:42,360 --> 00:16:43,759
So, he gave up

397
00:16:43,799 --> 00:16:44,919
and went to work in the city.

398
00:16:44,960 --> 00:16:45,840
But with all this equipment,

399
00:16:45,840 --> 00:16:46,919
I couldn't just let it sit idle.

400
00:16:47,559 --> 00:16:48,399
So I started
learning it from him.

401
00:16:50,000 --> 00:16:51,000
It smells so good.

402
00:16:51,200 --> 00:16:52,000
You're really amazing.

403
00:16:53,279 --> 00:16:54,519
Well, as people say,

404
00:16:54,919 --> 00:16:57,519
tea drinkers talk about the past,

405
00:16:58,240 --> 00:17:00,240
while coffee drinkers talk about the future.

406
00:17:00,360 --> 00:17:00,799
See?

407
00:17:01,120 --> 00:17:01,919
It's drawn all of you
young people here.

408
00:17:03,919 --> 00:17:05,200
Alright, take your time and enjoy.

409
00:17:05,279 --> 00:17:06,319
Call me if you need anything.

410
00:17:06,480 --> 00:17:07,160
We'll do, thanks Granny.
Thank you, Granny.

411
00:17:07,960 --> 00:17:09,119
Leave it to Granny Zhao,

412
00:17:09,279 --> 00:17:10,559
she can really match your Nanna.

413
00:17:11,400 --> 00:17:12,519
They chat whenever they're free.

414
00:17:12,599 --> 00:17:13,079
See,

415
00:17:13,359 --> 00:17:14,440
Granny Zhao knows that

416
00:17:14,680 --> 00:17:15,519
I can't stand pour-over.

417
00:17:16,920 --> 00:17:17,799
You know what,

418
00:17:18,400 --> 00:17:20,359
Granny Zhao's coffee-making skills

419
00:17:20,359 --> 00:17:20,960
are really good.

420
00:17:21,359 --> 00:17:22,720
It's just as good as the ones in Beijing.

421
00:17:24,000 --> 00:17:25,319
I've stayed in Beijing before too.

422
00:17:25,519 --> 00:17:26,039
Really?
Yeah!

423
00:17:27,160 --> 00:17:28,359
I stayed there for a while back then.

424
00:17:28,720 --> 00:17:30,200
Then coming here now,

425
00:17:30,319 --> 00:17:31,440
was it hard to get used to?

426
00:17:32,680 --> 00:17:34,200
I wasn't used to it at first.

427
00:17:34,960 --> 00:17:36,039
But later I found out,

428
00:17:36,480 --> 00:17:37,400
These big local cherries give

429
00:17:37,599 --> 00:17:38,640
aren't any worse than imported ones.

430
00:17:39,519 --> 00:17:40,160
Jujube cake

431
00:17:40,359 --> 00:17:42,039
can easily replace cheesecake.

432
00:17:42,640 --> 00:17:44,359
And those patterned buns

433
00:17:44,440 --> 00:17:45,440
can be a substitute for bagels.

434
00:17:45,720 --> 00:17:46,920
But don't you still miss

435
00:17:46,920 --> 00:17:48,119
the authentic originals sometimes?

436
00:17:49,920 --> 00:17:51,160
I used to fancy cheesecake

437
00:17:51,160 --> 00:17:52,000
very much.

438
00:17:52,240 --> 00:17:53,240
I wanted to eat it every single day.

439
00:17:53,440 --> 00:17:54,400
But now I know,

440
00:17:54,680 --> 00:17:55,920
I can live without it.

441
00:17:56,160 --> 00:17:57,839
I'm super adaptable to new environments.

442
00:17:58,519 --> 00:18:00,920
I've evolved a "Zhazha stomach".

443
00:18:01,200 --> 00:18:02,000
Zhazha stomach?

444
00:18:02,440 --> 00:18:03,440
Is that really a thing?

445
00:18:03,559 --> 00:18:04,079
Let me try.

446
00:18:10,920 --> 00:18:12,240
How's it any different from herbal medicine?

447
00:18:14,799 --> 00:18:16,440
Come on, what do you know?

448
00:18:17,920 --> 00:18:18,720
Have this sweet

449
00:18:18,720 --> 00:18:19,799
and shut your mouth up.

450
00:18:20,200 --> 00:18:21,559
I'll just stick to my instant coffee.

451
00:18:25,400 --> 00:18:26,000
Qing Ye,

452
00:18:26,279 --> 00:18:27,559
you're Xing Wu's cousin.

453
00:18:27,599 --> 00:18:28,599
How come I've never seen you
in Zhazhating before?

454
00:18:30,759 --> 00:18:32,200
My mom said I came here once

455
00:18:32,200 --> 00:18:32,920
when I was really little.

456
00:18:33,119 --> 00:18:34,440
After that, we were probably too busy,

457
00:18:34,519 --> 00:18:35,240
so we never came back.

458
00:18:35,720 --> 00:18:37,039
What kind of relatives are you guys?

459
00:18:37,200 --> 00:18:38,559
No matter what, relatives

460
00:18:38,559 --> 00:18:40,240
should still visit each other, huh?

461
00:18:41,079 --> 00:18:42,279
We aren't related by blood.

462
00:18:55,599 --> 00:18:56,440
Well...I see.

463
00:19:04,119 --> 00:19:04,599
Qing Ye,

464
00:19:05,240 --> 00:19:05,839
Fancy a drink?

465
00:19:06,599 --> 00:19:07,960
Granny Zhao has her own homemade liquor.

466
00:19:12,160 --> 00:19:13,720
Well, I'd better not.

467
00:19:14,640 --> 00:19:16,440
It's fine! It's not very strong.

468
00:19:16,480 --> 00:19:17,200
It won't hit you hard.

469
00:19:17,680 --> 00:19:18,279
Forget it.
She doesn't drink.

470
00:19:19,240 --> 00:19:19,759
What?

471
00:19:19,920 --> 00:19:20,960
She's not an adult?

472
00:19:21,079 --> 00:19:21,599
I am!

473
00:19:21,799 --> 00:19:22,759
She's an adult,

474
00:19:23,359 --> 00:19:24,200
but his tolerance isn't.

475
00:19:26,720 --> 00:19:27,640
If she's not drinking,

476
00:19:27,920 --> 00:19:28,519
will you?
I won't.

477
00:19:29,359 --> 00:19:30,559
I gotta work overtime at Shunyi tonight.

478
00:19:36,480 --> 00:19:37,319
Hello, Dr. Zhuang.

479
00:19:39,319 --> 00:19:40,039
It's broken again?

480
00:19:40,680 --> 00:19:41,319
Is it urgent?

481
00:19:42,039 --> 00:19:43,319
Okay, okay.

482
00:19:44,079 --> 00:19:44,680
I'll go, I'll go.

483
00:19:46,839 --> 00:19:47,960
I just don't get it.

484
00:19:48,680 --> 00:19:50,200
Why do they always come to you

485
00:19:50,359 --> 00:19:51,559
to fix things right before dark?

486
00:19:51,920 --> 00:19:52,640
This is the peak hour for
using electrical appliances.

487
00:19:53,759 --> 00:19:55,160
Dr. Zhuang's TV is broken.

488
00:19:55,319 --> 00:19:56,279
He said today's the finale.

489
00:19:56,640 --> 00:19:57,559
I'll be right back.

490
00:20:01,920 --> 00:20:02,519
Shu Han,

491
00:20:03,279 --> 00:20:04,920
he's gone, let's drink a little.

492
00:20:06,720 --> 00:20:07,200
Good.

493
00:20:30,319 --> 00:20:31,920
We've started drinking. Hurry up.

494
00:20:32,839 --> 00:20:33,680
Don't let her drink too much.

495
00:20:38,359 --> 00:20:39,160
Many thanks, Wu.

496
00:20:39,920 --> 00:20:40,920
Have some water, here.

497
00:20:41,680 --> 00:20:42,519
Thanks, Dr. Zhuang.

498
00:20:43,599 --> 00:20:44,240
So, how is it?

499
00:20:44,599 --> 00:20:45,440
Is it a major problem?

500
00:20:48,160 --> 00:20:48,960
It's minor, actually.

501
00:20:49,799 --> 00:20:50,680
So that means I can

502
00:20:50,680 --> 00:20:51,839
watch the finale, right?

503
00:20:52,160 --> 00:20:52,680
Don't worry.

504
00:20:53,039 --> 00:20:53,839
I'll definitely make sure
you watch the finale today.

505
00:20:55,240 --> 00:20:56,160
That's great.

506
00:20:56,480 --> 00:20:58,160
I was so worried I'd miss it.

507
00:20:59,759 --> 00:21:00,440
How much?

508
00:21:01,640 --> 00:21:02,920
Forget about the money.

509
00:21:02,960 --> 00:21:03,519
No charge.

510
00:21:04,160 --> 00:21:04,920
My Grandma said,

511
00:21:05,279 --> 00:21:06,440
last time she came you for medicated patching

512
00:21:06,440 --> 00:21:07,480
and you only charged her for the labor.

513
00:21:07,720 --> 00:21:08,759
Th...This old lady.

514
00:21:09,359 --> 00:21:10,599
Still couldn't fool her.

515
00:21:10,680 --> 00:21:11,519
Such expensive medicine,

516
00:21:11,759 --> 00:21:13,000
and you only charged 10 yuan.

517
00:21:13,599 --> 00:21:14,640
Only a fool would believe it.

518
00:21:16,200 --> 00:21:18,119
I just wanna save you some money.

519
00:21:18,400 --> 00:21:19,559
We're all neighbors here.

520
00:21:20,200 --> 00:21:21,039
No need to be so polite.

521
00:21:21,799 --> 00:21:22,519
Business's business.

522
00:21:22,960 --> 00:21:24,359
She doesn't like owing people favors.

523
00:21:24,640 --> 00:21:25,240
Neither do I.
We're even now, huh.

524
00:21:26,720 --> 00:21:28,319
Fine, have it your way then.

525
00:21:29,920 --> 00:21:31,039
The two of you

526
00:21:31,480 --> 00:21:32,279
— cut from the same cloth.

527
00:21:32,799 --> 00:21:33,640
In your hearts,

528
00:21:34,079 --> 00:21:35,240
each of you is sharper than the other.

529
00:21:36,759 --> 00:21:37,279
You rest up
I'll call you when it's fixed.

530
00:21:38,359 --> 00:21:38,759
Good.

531
00:21:39,039 --> 00:21:39,920
I...I've still got medicine
brewing out back.

532
00:21:40,799 --> 00:21:41,400
You go ahead.

533
00:21:51,079 --> 00:21:51,680
[Don't worry.]

534
00:21:56,920 --> 00:21:57,440
[Girl,]
[you really start drinking]

535
00:21:58,119 --> 00:21:59,400
[with your sister-in-law?]

536
00:21:59,440 --> 00:22:00,720
[Why didn't you call me over?]

537
00:22:00,839 --> 00:22:02,279
[When we girls drink,]

538
00:22:02,480 --> 00:22:03,079
[how are we supposed]

539
00:22:03,240 --> 00:22:04,240
[to have girl talk if you're here?]

540
00:22:04,400 --> 00:22:05,680
[Kyle, stop shouting nonsense.]

541
00:22:05,799 --> 00:22:06,920
[You're making me sound old.]

542
00:22:07,279 --> 00:22:09,000
[You two became besties so quickly?]

543
00:22:09,279 --> 00:22:09,920
[My goodness.]

544
00:22:09,920 --> 00:22:11,319
[Sisters-in-law? Soul sisters!]

545
00:22:12,279 --> 00:22:14,039
[Don't forget to hand out flyers tomorrow.]

546
00:22:17,119 --> 00:22:17,559
Come on.

547
00:22:19,720 --> 00:22:20,559
Great.

548
00:22:21,759 --> 00:22:22,200
Cheers.
Cheers.

549
00:22:27,240 --> 00:22:28,039
You really have no idea.

550
00:22:28,160 --> 00:22:29,559
Xing Wu used to be even busier.

551
00:22:30,079 --> 00:22:31,559
Every time, he'd get a bite of a meal,

552
00:22:31,599 --> 00:22:32,359
then someone would call him away.

553
00:22:32,559 --> 00:22:33,920
He'd back after helping out, eat a bite,

554
00:22:33,960 --> 00:22:34,799
then get called out again.

555
00:22:35,200 --> 00:22:35,920
By the end of the day,
he couldn't even finish a single meal.

556
00:22:37,000 --> 00:22:37,720
It would turn completely cold.

557
00:22:38,359 --> 00:22:39,119
Shu Han,

558
00:22:39,680 --> 00:22:40,759
did you and Xing Wu

559
00:22:40,839 --> 00:22:41,920
grow up together?

560
00:22:42,440 --> 00:22:43,079
No.

561
00:22:43,480 --> 00:22:44,920
We've known each other for about

562
00:22:45,000 --> 00:22:45,599
2 years.

563
00:22:46,839 --> 00:22:47,440
2 years?

564
00:22:48,920 --> 00:22:49,839
I've heard from Auntie

565
00:22:49,920 --> 00:22:51,480
